---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const otherRoles = [
  { name: "COO / Operations Leader", href: "/use-case/coo" },
  { name: "Program Manager", href: "/use-case/program-manager" },
  { name: "Project Manager", href: "/use-case/project-manager" },
  { name: "Engineering Leader", href: "/use-case/engineering-leader" },
  { name: "Team Lead", href: "/use-case/team-lead" },
  { name: "Account Executive", href: "/use-case/account-executive" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="In Parallel for Strategy & PMO Teams"
  description="Strategic goals connected to operational execution in real time. Portfolio-level execution health, early drift warnings, and quarterly reviews from actual data."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 md:pt-44 md:pb-24">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-4xl text-center">
      <p class="section-eyebrow mb-4 scroll-reveal">Use case</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl tracking-tight leading-[1.05] mb-8 scroll-reveal">
        In Parallel for Strategy &amp; PMO Teams
      </h1>
      <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-xl md:text-2xl max-w-3xl mx-auto font-display-regular leading-snug scroll-reveal">
        You set the strategy. Then you watch it slowly disconnect from reality.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section class="pb-20 md:pb-32">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-3xl">
      <p class="section-eyebrow mb-4 scroll-reveal">The problem</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight mb-8 scroll-reveal">
        Strategy without execution visibility is just a presentation.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-ip-white-muted text-lg leading-relaxed scroll-reveal">
        <p>
          You spend weeks crafting the strategic plan. You align leadership. You cascade goals. And then the plan enters the operational layer &mdash; where meetings happen, priorities shift, and reality takes over. Within weeks, the connection between strategy and execution starts to fray.
        </p>
        <p>
          The problem isn't that people ignore strategy. It's that there's no mechanism to keep strategy connected to the daily decisions that shape execution. Quarterly reviews become exercises in narrative construction &mdash; teams curate stories about progress rather than reporting what actually happened.
        </p>
        <p>
          As a PMO or strategy leader, you're accountable for ensuring that what the organization does aligns with what it decided to do. But your visibility depends on people voluntarily reporting up &mdash; and by the time you see the picture, it's weeks old.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How In Parallel Helps -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-ip-navy-light">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-5xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-16 scroll-reveal">
        <p class="section-eyebrow mb-4">How In Parallel helps</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight">
          Connect strategy to what&rsquo;s actually happening.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-ip-navy-surface border border-ip-border rounded-xl p-6 scroll-reveal">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-3 text-white">Strategy-execution connection</h3>
          <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Strategic goals are connected to operational execution in real time. You see how daily decisions and meeting outcomes map to your strategic priorities &mdash; without anyone having to make that connection manually.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-ip-navy-surface border border-ip-border rounded-xl p-6 scroll-reveal">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-3 text-white">Data-driven quarterly reviews</h3>
          <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Quarterly reviews draw from actual meeting data and execution patterns, not curated narratives. You see what happened, when it was decided, and how it connects to strategic objectives.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-ip-navy-surface border border-ip-border rounded-xl p-6 scroll-reveal">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-3 text-white">Portfolio-level execution health</h3>
          <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            See execution health across all initiatives in your portfolio. Execution scores, progress patterns, and risk flags give you an honest picture of organizational delivery.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-ip-navy-surface border border-ip-border rounded-xl p-6 scroll-reveal">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg mb-3 text-white">Early strategic drift warnings</h3>
          <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Know when execution drifts from strategic intent while there's still time to correct course. In Parallel surfaces the gap between what was planned and what's emerging from operational reality.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pull Quote -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-3xl text-center scroll-reveal">
      <blockquote class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight leading-[1.15] text-white">
        &ldquo;Strategy without execution visibility is just a presentation.&rdquo;
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- See It In Action -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-ip-navy-light">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-3xl">
      <p class="section-eyebrow mb-4 scroll-reveal">See it in action</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight mb-8 scroll-reveal">
        A typical quarter with In Parallel
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-ip-white-muted text-lg leading-relaxed scroll-reveal">
        <p>
          Early in Q2. You've set three strategic priorities for the year. In Parallel shows you that execution across Priority 1 is strong &mdash; teams are making consistent decisions that align with the goal. Priority 2 is drifting &mdash; two programs have started making trade-offs that favor short-term delivery over the strategic objective.
        </p>
        <p>
          You flag the drift to the program sponsors before the midpoint review. They adjust course in the next steering meeting. In Parallel captures that decision and propagates it to the affected teams. No slide deck. No email chain. The correction happens through the normal operating rhythm.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the quarterly review, you present a portfolio view drawn from actual execution data. You show decision patterns, execution scores, and drift trajectories. The leadership team makes resource allocation decisions based on what's real, not what was curated for them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Also Explore -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl tracking-tight mb-8 text-center scroll-reveal">
        Also explore
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 scroll-reveal">
        {otherRoles.map((role) => (
          <a
            href={role.href}
            class="border border-ip-border rounded-full px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-display text-ip-white-muted hover:border-ip-lime/40 hover:text-white transition-colors"
          >
            {role.name}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-ip-navy-light">
    <div class="container-ip text-center scroll-reveal">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight mb-6">
        Close the strategy-execution gap.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ip-white-muted text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        See how In Parallel connects strategic intent to operational reality. 30-minute demo.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/demo" class="btn-primary">
          Book a demo
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/use-case" class="btn-secondary">
          All use cases
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
